<paragraph id="C70597710D2575506BD0B7A467B9A2D0" blockId="4.[151,475,1509,1535]" box="[151,475,1509,1535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<heading id="9C4D201D0D2575506BD0B7A467B9A2D0" bold="true" box="[151,475,1509,1535]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" reason="1">
<emphasis id="F5CE4B630D2575506BD0B7A467B9A2D0" bold="true" box="[151,475,1509,1535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="00BAECF20D2575506BA9B7A467B9A2D0" authority="Fabricius" authorityName="Fabricius" box="[238,475,1509,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Brassolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5CE4B630D2575506BA9B7A4673FA2D0" bold="true" box="[238,349,1509,1535]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Brassolis</emphasis>
Fabricius
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C70597710D2575506BD0B46E6348A0E3" blockId="4.[151,1436,1583,1996]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Robust-bodied, medium size (male FW length from 60.5 mm (
<taxonomicName id="00BAECF20D25755068DFB47165BEA166" box="[920,988,1584,1609]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Brassolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dinizi">
<emphasis id="F5CE4B630D25755068DFB47165BEA166" box="[920,988,1584,1609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">dinizi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<emphasis id="F5CE4B630D25755068A8B4716265A166" box="[1007,1031,1584,1609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">to</emphasis>
82.7 mm for (
<taxonomicName id="00BAECF20D2575506FFCB4716365A166" box="[1211,1287,1584,1609]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Brassolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="astyra">
<emphasis id="F5CE4B630D2575506FFCB4716365A166" box="[1211,1287,1584,1609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">astyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 
<figureCitation id="5F818BF40D2575506E65B46E630FA166" box="[1314,1389,1583,1609]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,257,1301,1325]" captionTargetBox="[169,1419,274,1275]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[153,1430,264,1309]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Brassolis species in dorsal (left) and ventral (right) views. (A &amp; B) Male and female B. sophorae from French Guiana. (C &amp; D) Female and male B. sophorae from Ecuador. (E &amp; F) Male and female B. haenschi from Ecuador. (G) Male B. sophorae from Trinidad. (H) Male B. sophorae from Peru. (I &amp; J) Male and female B. dinizi from Paraiba and Ceará respectively (Brazil). (K) Male B. sophorae from Santa Catarina (Brazil). (L) Male B. sophorae from Paraguay." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188450/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number id="717285560D2575506E1CB46E630FA166" box="[1371,1389,1583,1609]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2.3">2</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="5F818BF40D2575506E3CB46E63EEA166" box="[1403,1420,1583,1609]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,257,1913,1937]" captionTargetBox="[223,1316,798,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[218,1348,783,1910]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Brassolis species, in dorsal (left) and ventral (right) views (except for C). (A &amp; B) Male and female B. isthmia from Panama. (C) Male B. isthmia from Costa Rica. (D) Male of granadensis from Colombia. (E) Detail showing head and proboscis of B. isthmia from Panama. (F &amp; G) Male and female B. astyra from Rio de Janeiro (Brazil). (H) Male B. astyra from Rio Grande do Sul (Brazil)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188451/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">3</figureCitation>
). Antennae short, strongly clubbed. Reduced, non-functional proboscis (
<figureCitation id="5F818BF40D25755068AEB4176253A15F" box="[1001,1073,1622,1648]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,257,1913,1937]" captionTargetBox="[223,1316,798,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[218,1348,783,1910]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Brassolis species, in dorsal (left) and ventral (right) views (except for C). (A &amp; B) Male and female B. isthmia from Panama. (C) Male B. isthmia from Costa Rica. (D) Male of granadensis from Colombia. (E) Detail showing head and proboscis of B. isthmia from Panama. (F &amp; G) Male and female B. astyra from Rio de Janeiro (Brazil). (H) Male B. astyra from Rio Grande do Sul (Brazil)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188451/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number id="717285560D2575506F65B4176253A15F" box="[1058,1073,1622,1648]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
E). Tibial spurs absent in both sexes. Dorsal FW brown with an orange, or orange and white postmedial band, depending on the species. Dorsal HW brown with or without an orange postmedial band, depending on the species. Males with a small, narrow patch of androconial scales below vein Cu 
<number id="717285560D25755069BAB48B6569A1CB" box="[765,779,1738,1764]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2.0">2</number>
(
<figureCitation id="5F818BF40D257550685AB48B6505A1CB" box="[797,871,1738,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,255,1907,1931]" captionTargetBox="[202,1408,195,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,157,1880]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Wing characters. (A) Brassolis dizini. (B) B. astyra. (C) B. haenschi. (D) Dynastor darius." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188455/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number id="717285560D2575506810B48B6505A1CB" box="[855,871,1738,1764]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
B, character 
<number id="717285560D2575506F44B48B6247A1CB" box="[1027,1061,1738,1764]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="16.0">16</number>
). Sexes similar in color, males smaller than females. FW basal, costal margin in-curved in males, bowed in females. Ventral HW brown stippled with white; eyespots in cells Sc+R 
<number id="717285560D25755069DDB55664C6A01E" box="[666,676,1815,1841]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
and Cu 
<number id="717285560D2575506841B5566572A01E" box="[774,784,1815,1841]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
variable in size. Male and female genitalia remarkably uniform across species. Male gnathos absent (unique within 
<taxonomicName id="00BAECF20D257550681DB57F65B4A077" box="[858,982,1854,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Brassolini">Brassolini</taxonomicName>
); valva broad, distally curved and with apical serration (
<figureCitation id="5F818BF40D2575506A1EB52567FFA051" box="[345,413,1892,1918]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1625,1649]" captionTargetBox="[157,1409,196,1582]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,164,1735]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male characters. Scale bars, 1 mm. Labial palp in lateral view. (A) Bia actorion. (B) Brassolis sophorae. (C) Dynastor darius. Tegumen in dorsal view. (D) B. astyra. Genitalic capsule in lateral view. (E) D. darius. (F) B. sophorae. Tegumen and uncus in lateral view. (G) D. macrosiris. Phallus in lateral view. (H) D. napoleon. Juxta in ventral view. (I) B. astyra. (J) D. napoleon. Phallus in ventral view. (K) D. darius. (L) B. haenschi. (M) B. granadensis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188456/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number id="717285560D2575506AC8B52567FFA051" box="[399,413,1892,1918]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
F); phallus with minute spines along the shaft and usually two to three setae on the edge of the vesica. Female sterigma projected as a flap posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="5F818BF40D25755068C9B5CA65BAA08A" box="[910,984,1931,1957]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,256,1456,1480]" captionTargetBox="[153,1412,201,1455]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,127,1497]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Female characters. Scale bars, 1 mm. Female distal tarsomere in ventral view (details of pulvillar process omitted). (A) Dynastor darius. Sterigma in ventral view. (B) D. darius. (C) B. isthmia. (D) B. astyra. (E) B. dinizi. Posterior lobes of papillae annales in lateral view. (F) Elymnias hypermnestra. (G) D. napoleon. (H) B. haenschi. Note that the lamella antevaginalis is not visible in C, D, and E due to the orientation of the drawing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188457/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number id="717285560D257550688FB5CA65BAA08A" box="[968,984,1931,1957]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
C, D, E); anterior section of sterigma (lamella antevaginalis) thin and generally continuous, forming a ‘loop’. Corpus bursa lacking signa.
</paragraph>
